Install Java 19 and Maven 4 (for Ubuntu 22.04)

Run script:
java.sh
*(perhaps you have to do: sudo apt install openjfx)


Install chromedriver

Upgrade and check version if exist:
sudo apt-get update && apt-get upgrade
chromedriver

If there are differences between chrome and chromedriver versions:
https://chromedriver.storage.googleapis.com/index.html

Run script:
driver.sh



Install app

Put folder in home directory:
bash teststation/java.sh
bash teststation/install.sh

Delete icon:
bash teststation/delete.sh







